itional 205 beds.<ref name=\"gate.ahram.org.eg\"/>\n\nEgypt\u2019s Military Medical Academy was founded in 1979 with the purpose of educating and training medical officers in all branches of Egypt\u2019s armed forces.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mma.edu.eg/History.aspx|title=\u0646\u0628\u0630\u0629 \u062a\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062e\u064a\u0629|last=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0629|first=\u0627\u0644\u0623\u0643\u0627\u062f\u064a\u0645\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0628\u064a\u0629|website=www.mma.edu.eg|access-date=2017-05-11}}</ref> The facility is located on Ihsan Abdul Quddus Street in [[Cairo|Cairo.]] It is associated with the Armed Forces Medical College, founded in 1827.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afcm.ac.eg/ar/|title=\u0643\u0644\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0628 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0644\u062d\u0629|website=www.afcm.ac.eg|access-date=2017-05-11}}</ref> This was the Middle East\u2019s first modern school of medicine and was a product of Egypt\u2019s newly established Military Department of Health during the administration of [[Muhammad Ali of Egypt|Muhammad Ali Pasha]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afcm.ac.eg/ar/History.aspx|title=\u0646\u0628\u0630\u0629 \u062a\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062e\u064a\u0629|website=www.afcm.ac.eg|access-date=2017-05-11}}</ref>\n\n== Spurious claims about HIV/AIDS == \nAt a press conference in February 2014 by Egyptian Gen. [[Ibrahim Abdel-Atti]], chief of the medical branch, falsely claimed that the Egyptian Army had \"defeated [[AIDS]]... with a rate of 100%\" as well as [[hepatitis C]]. Abdel-Atti claimed to construct a method to extract the disease and break it into amino acids, \"so that the virus becomes nutrition for the body instead of disease.\" It is said{{By whom|date=August 2016}} that this treatment process could take anywhere between 20 days and 6 months to cure having no side effects. Egypt intends to delay exporting their new technology to generate medical tourism into the country. The claims were eventually confirmed to be false.<ref name=\"Berman-AIDS cured\">{{cite news|last=Berman|first=Lazar|title=AIDS cured! (says Egypt\u2019s military)|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/aids-cured-says-egypts-military/|accessdate=26 February 2014|newspaper=Times of Israel|date=26 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Ahram-AIDS\">{{cite news|title=Egypt presidential advisor: Army health devices for virus C & AIDS must comply with int'l standards|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/95121/Egypt/Politics-/UPDATED-Egypt-presidential-advisor-Army-health-dev.aspx|accessdate=26 February 2014|newspaper=Ahram Online|date=25 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Inoyori-AIDS\">{{cite news|last=Inoyori |first=Ryan |title=HIV Cure: 'Complete Cure' Machine Invented To Treat Hepatitis C And HIV With 95% to 100% Guarantee |url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/540619/20140226/hiv-cure-complete-machine-invented-treat-hepatitis.htm |accessdate=26 February 2014 |newspaper=International Business Times |date=26 February 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227161957/https://au.ibtimes.com/articles/540619/20140226/hiv-cure-complete-machine-invented-treat-hepatitis.htm |archivedate=27 February 2014 }}</ref>\n\n== Structure ==\nThe Medical Services Department runs about 48 fixed military hospitals, listed below.\n\nThe Army's Medical Corps may have 27 Field Medical Battalions (1st to 27th); 107 Field Medical Companies (201st to 308th); three 3 Hospital Ships, and four Hospital Barges\n\n=== List of Military Hospitals ===\n\nSource is the Egyptian Ministry of Defence site:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903215801/https://www.mod.gov.eg/ModWebSite/ServiceDetailsAr.aspx?id=5|title=\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0634\u0641\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0644\u062d\u0629|date=2019-09-03|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitab