ess-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> \n\nRaja Sardar Singh of Khetri constructed many buildings in Kotputli. For example, Sardar School and Sardar Zanana Hospital were made by local Gurjar bodies in conjunction with the Tijoriwala family. Many schools and hospitals have emerged in Kotputli since. Many business opportunities also exist in Kotputli, such as Kotputli Cement Works<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adityabirla.com/media/press-reports/excellence-no-finish-line|title=Excellence \u2013 No Finish Line|website=abg.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.birlacorporation.com/plants.html|title=Birla Corporation|website=www.birlacorporation.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>. \n\nThe closest village to Kotputli is Kuhada. The municipality is 70 km away from [[Alwar]], 105 km away from [[Jaipur]] and 128 km from [[Gurgaon]]. Nearby places to visit include [[Bhangarh]], Siliserh, Baleshwar historic temple (40 km away), Baba Bhairon temple village, Khuhada [[Sariska]], and [[Sarund Mata]]. The PEER Baba ki Samadhi and Shiva temple located in KUJOTA (pujari AJAY YOGI PANWAR) is also a 300-year-old monument. It is a place of worship for both Hindus and Muslims in the area. A great fair is organized every year on the sixth of Bhadrapad (Hindi Month). Many people participate in the fair every year. Advocate Nemsingh Gurjar also telling about it. \n\nKotputli is home to many government and non-government higher education institutions, including Lal Bahadur Shastri Govt. PG College, Shri Krishna PG Law College, Tagore PG Law College, and Hans Law College<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oruschool.in/blocks/kotputli-jaipur|title=List of schools in Kotputli, Jaipur block {{!}} OruSchool.In|website=oruschool.in|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>. \n\n==Population==\nThe Kotputli Municipality has a population of 49,202 as of the [[2011 Census of India|Census India 2011.]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.censusindia2011.com/rajasthan/jaipur/kotputli-population.html|title=Kotputli Tehsil Population Jaipur, Rajasthan, List of Villages & Towns in Kotputli Tehsil|website=Censusindia2011.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> The municipality has 26,051 males and 23,151 females.\n\n==Demographics==\nThe population is made up of 52.7% males and 47.3% females<ref name=\":0\" />. 97.6% of the region identifies as Hindu and 2.0% as Muslim, with Christians, Sikhs, and Jains making up the remaining population. Kotputli has an average literacy rate of 60.6%, higher than the national average of 59.5%; male literacy is 71.5%, and female literacy is 48.6%<ref name=\":0\" />. 88.1% of the population lives in the city while 11.9% lives rurally. In Kotputli, 15.5% of the population is under 6 years of age.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Geography and climate==\n\nKotputli is located at 27.705479\u00b0N 76.190969\u00b0E. It has an average elevation of 439 metres (1440&nbsp;feet).\n\n<br>\n{{Weather box\n|location = Kotputli\n|metric first = Yes\n|single line = Yes\n|Jan high C = 25\n|Feb high C = 28\n|Mar high C = 34\n|Apr high C = 38\n|May high C = 41\n|Jun high C = 40\n|Jul high C = 36\n|Aug high C = 34\n|Sep high C = 36\n|Oct high C = 36\n|Nov high C = 31\n|Dec high C = 27\n|year high C =\n|Jan low C = 8\n|Feb low C = 12\n|Mar low C = 18\n|Apr low C = 23\n|May low C = 27\n|Jun low C = 29\n|Jul low C = 27\n|Aug low C = 26\n|Sep low C = 25\n|Oct low C = 20\n|Nov low C = 15\n|Dec low C = 9\n|year low C =\n|Jan precipitation cm = 0.35\n|Feb precipitation cm = 0.27\n|Mar precipitation cm = 0.32\n|Apr precipitation cm = 0.35\n|May precipitation cm = 0.6\n|Jun precipitation cm = 3.26\n|Jul precipitation cm = 8.89\n|Aug precipitation cm = 6.44\n|Sep precipitation cm = 3.42\n|Oct precipitation cm = 0.45\n|Nov precipitation cm = 0.07\n|Dec precipitation cm = 0.06\n|year precipitation cm =\n|source = Foreca\n|date=June 2011}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Alwar]]\n* [[Jaipur]]\n* [[Shahpura, Jaipur|Shahpura]]\n* [[Neem Ka Thana]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Jaipur district]]\n", "name_user": "AreliOneAreliOne", "label": "safe", "comment": "Linked to Marwari peoples of India", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kotputli"}
